This paper deals with the analysis of a multicell multiuser MIMO downlink system, which involves the use of random beamforming as the transmission scheme. The paper focuses on the effects of intercell and intracell interference, which are important topics in the field of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of scheduling policies to maintain fairness among users and obtain multiuser diversity gain, which are topics in the field of signal processing (cs.SI) and multimedia systems (cs.MM). Finally, the paper analyzes the scaling laws of the system, which is a topic in the field of game theory (cs.GT).
